{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1768492354,"nonce":"JGcHHh1siM1yV8UXu66aHlt3KiY=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87jk-bQ","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/3","origin":"github"},"title":"Document codespace bootstrap instructions","message":"## Problem\n\nSetting up the workspace in a GitHub Codespace requires manual intervention for several dependencies and configurations that are not documented.\n\n## Steps Attempted\n\n1. **Installed vcstool** - Required to import repositories, but not available via apt on Ubuntu 24.04\n   - Solution: Installed via pip: `pip3 install vcstool`\n\n2. **SSH to HTTPS conversion** - Default `configs/core.repos` uses SSH URLs which fail in codespaces without SSH keys\n   - Solution: Converted all URLs from `git@github.com:owner/repo.git` to `https://github.com/owner/repo.git`\n\n3. **ROS 2 Jazzy** - Not pre-installed in codespace\n   - Solution: Full ROS 2 installation required (~1GB+ download)\n   - Command: `sudo apt-get install -y ros-jazzy-desktop`\n\n4. **Colcon** - Build tool not installed\n   - Solution: `sudo apt-get install -y python3-colcon-common-extensions`\n\n5. **rosdep** - Dependency management tool not installed\n   - Solution: `sudo apt-get install -y python3-rosdep`\n   - Initialization: `sudo rosdep init \u0026\u0026 rosdep update`\n\n6. **Python dependencies** - Missing Python modules for message generation\n   - `empy==3.3.4` - Required for ROS message generation\n   - `catkin_pkg` - Required for package parsing\n   - `lark` - Parser dependency\n\n## Proposed Solution\n\nCreate a bootstrap script or document the setup process for codespaces:\n\n### Option 1: Bootstrap Script\nCreate `scripts/bootstrap_codespace.sh`:\n```bash\n# Install ROS 2 and dependencies for codespace development\n\n# 1. Install ROS 2 Jazzy\n# 2. Install vcstool via pip\n# 3. Install colcon\n# 4. Install and initialize rosdep\n# 5. Install Python dependencies\n# 6. Convert SSH URLs to HTTPS in all .repos files\n```\n\n### Option 2: Documentation\nAdd a `CODESPACE_SETUP.md` with step-by-step instructions.\n\n### Option 3: Dev Container Configuration\nCreate `.devcontainer/devcontainer.json` with postCreateCommand that handles all setup automatically.\n\n## Related Files\n- `configs/core.repos` (and other .repos files) - Should support HTTPS URLs by default\n- `scripts/setup.sh` - Could check for and install missing dependencies\n- `README.md` - Should mention codespace-specific setup","files":null}]}